com.github.javactic

Interface Every<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the Every
    All Superinterfaces:
    IntFunction<T>, Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Many, One

    public interface Every<T>
extends Iterable<T>, IntFunction<T>
    An ordered, immutable, non-empty collection of elements. Class Every has two and only two subtypes: One and Many. A One contains exactly one element. A Many contains two or more elements. Thus no way exists for an Every to contain zero elements.

    Motivation for Everys

    Although Every is a general-purpose, non-empty ordered collection, it was motivated by the desire to enable easy accumulation of errors in Ors. Please refer to the original documentation for the Scalactic library on Ors and Everys.
    Author:
    mvh
